<A NAME="tbreopos"><EM>Table 7:</EM> Positions for REOSC/CCD-UMass</A>
<PRE>

Angle     Stage  Orders  Wavelength Range    Lines
                               [&Aring;]
<P><HR><P>
354&#176;35&#180;   4.09   34-41   5408-6699
354&#176;      4.09   36-45   4933-6322
353&#176;30&#180;   4.09   40-51   4358-5682
353&#176;      4.09   44-55   4044-5159

353&#176;10&#180;   3.0                         Hbeta, [Oiii]4959
353&#176;10&#180;   4.09                        Hbeta, [Oiii]4959
353&#176;10&#180;   5.0                         Hbeta, [Oiii]4959,5007
353&#176;10&#180;   5.15                        Hbeta, gamma, delta
353&#176;10&#180;   7.5                         Hgamma, Hdelta [Oiii]4959
<P><HR><P>

The chip DOES NOT cover the free spectral range
of the orders in one exposure, hence there will
always be gaps. The wavelength range provided
is just an approximation based up on the Free
Spectral Range of the orders.

<P><HR><P>
</PRE>
 
<P><HR><A HREF="echelle.html">Return to Echelle Manual</A><HR><P>

