<HTML>
<TITLE>Figure 4: Blaze Function</TITLE>

<A HREF="echelle.html">Return to Echelle Manual</A>

<P><HR><P>
<A NAME="fgblaz">Figure 4: Blaze Function</A> <P>

 <P><A NAME="fgbl_top">(<EM> Top</EM>)</A>The relative intensities in
the first order of the two current cross dispersers (A &amp; B), and
two that the observatory is considering purchasing (C &amp; D). The
lines are plotted only within the order free spectral range for each
grating. Alpha is the angle of incidence upon the grating.

<IMG SRC="fig_int_a.gif" WIDTH=573 HEIGHT=537 > <P>

<P><HR><P>

 <P><A NAME="fgbl_bot">(<EM>Bottom</EM>)</A> An approximation of the
qualitative form of the blaze function in the echelle orders.  This is
the relative intensity function caused by the main echelle grating,
and since all of the order numbers are large, the functional
appearance changes little with order.

<IMG SRC="fig_int_f.gif" WIDTH=550 HEIGHT=529 >

<P><HR><P>

</HTML>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>WT14-B38-9</DOCNO>
