<TITLE>Seminar Schedule</TITLE>

<P><A NAME="current"><IMG SRC="../Gifs/redball.gif"></A> The Spring
Semester is over, and the seminar schedule now takes a break and will
resume in the <A HREF="./Sem_Fal95.html">fall</A>.  If you want to
know what you missed, read on, and please come back in September.  <P>

<H2>
IA-UNAM-Ensenada 1995<BR>
Spring Seminar Schedule:
</H2>
<IMG SRC="../Gifs/redball.gif"> marks upcoming seminar(s).
<IMG SRC="../Gifs/hrainbow.gif" ALIGN=center 
ALT="------------------------------------------------------------">
<P>
    
<DL>

<DT> Fri Feb 10 -- <EM>Eric Michel</EM> (Observatoire de Paris, Meudon)
<DD> "Por Que Tiemblan las Estrellas?"

<DT> Fri Feb 17 -- <EM>Dennis Mammana</EM> 
(Fleet Space Center) 
<DD> "Stars are for Everyone: Bringing the Universe Down to Earth"

<DT> Wed Feb 22 -- <EM>Kurt Marti</EM> (UCSD-Chemistry)
<DD> "The Orion Phenomonon: Radiation in the Early Solar System"

<DT> Thu Mar 2 -- <EM>Paul Etzel</EM> (SDSU) 
<DD> "Spectroscopic Studies of Mass Transfer in non-Degenerate Binaries"

<DT> Wed Mar 15 -- <EM>Ron Angione</EM> (SDSU) 
<DD> "Proposed 2.5-m Telescope &amp; Research at Mt Laguna Observatory"

<DT> Fri Mar 17 -- <EM>Chris Flynn</EM> (Nordita, Copenhagen, Denmark)
<DD> "Deep HST images: Dark Matter in the Halo and Disk,
      the Luminosity Function and Microlensing

<DT> Wed Mar 29 -- <EM>Mary Barsony</EM> (UC-Riverside)
<DD> "The Youngest Protostars"

<DT> Wed Apr 5 -- <EM>Bob Leach</EM> (SDSU)
<DD> "Recent Developments in CCD Camera Systems"

<DT> Fri Apr 7 -- 
     <EM>Roberto V&aacute;zquez</EM> (IA-UNAM-Ens.)
<DD> <STRONG>PUBLIC LECTURE - 7 pm</STRONG><BR>
     "Las Computadoras en la Investigacion Astron&oacute;mica"

<DT> Mon Apr 10 -- <EM>Morrie Barembaum</EM> (SDSU)
<DD> "Eclipsing Binary System"

<DT> Tue Apr 18 -- <EM>John Meaburn</EM> (Manchester) 
<DD> "Shocks in Everything"

<DT> Wed Apr 19 -- <EM>Emilio Mollinari</EM> (Obs. di Brera, Milano)
<DD> "The Luminosity Function of Elliptical Galaxies in Distant Clusters"

<DT> Fri Apr 21 -- <EM>Luis Carrasco</EM> (IA-UNAM/INAOE)
<DD> "Radial Gradients in Elliptical Galaxies"

<DT> Tue May 9 -- <EM>Warren Miller</EM> (UNAM-DF)
<DD> "Unravelling the Mysteries of the Diffuse ISM"

<DT> Fri May 12 -- <EM>Jerry Wasserburg</EM> (Caltech/Div. of Geological &amp; Planetary Sciences)
<DD> "Circumstellar Dust Grains In Meteorite/AGB Stars And Stellar Processes"

<DT> Tue May 16 -- <EM>Alberto Cordero</EM> (UAP)
<DD> "Evaluacion de Bi-Ronchi-Gramas por Integracion Numerica"

<DT> Thu May 18 -- <EM>Dave Crawford</EM> (KPNO)
<DD> "New Generation Small Telescopes and GNAT as Resources for 
      Astronomy and Education"

<DT> Wed May 24 -- <EM>Virginia Trimble</EM> (UC-Irvine)
<DD> "The Existence and Nature of Dark Matter"

<DT> Wed May 31 -- <EM>Luis Aguilar</EM> (IA-UNAM-Ens.)
<DD> "La Evolucion de Galaxias Elipticas en Cumulos: Experimentos 
	de N-Cuerpos"

<DT> Fri Jun 2 -- <EM>Juan Echevarr&iacute;a</EM> (IA-UNAM-Ens.)
<DD> <STRONG>PUBLIC LECTURE - 7 pm</STRONG><BR>
     "Estrellas Binarias Interactuantes"

<DT> Tue Jun 6 -- <EM>Hrant Tovmassian</EM> (INAOE)
<DD> "Observations of OB Stellar Associations with the Glazar Space Telescope"

<DT> Tue Jun 13 -- <EM>Carlos Chavarria-K</EM> (UNAM-DF)
<DD> "Descubrimientos Recientes Sobre Estrellas T-Tauri Desnudas(WTTS)"

<DT> Wed Jun 14 -- <EM>Judy Cohen</EM> (Caltech)
<DD> "The KECK Low Resolution Imaging Spectrograph: Preliminary 
     Results on Gravitational Lenses &amp; Deep Galaxy Redshift Surveys"

</DL>

<P>All seminars are at 12:00 noon in the auditorium, unless otherwise
specified, and feature coffee and cookies.<P>

<P>
<IMG SRC="../Gifs/hrainbow.gif" ALIGN=center 
ALT="------------------------------------------------------------">
