<title>Mauricio Reyes Ruiz</title>

<body>

<body background="space3.gif" text="#ffff00" link="00f0ff"
vlink="#ffffff">

<h1>Mauricio Reyes Ruiz</h1>
<p>
Hello! Translating the picture was the hardest part!
<p>
<p>
<center>
<IMG SRC="brain.gif"> 
<pre>
</center>

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<ul>
<li>I was born in :  <a href="http://www.tij.cetys.mx/infotij/infotij.html">
Tijuana </a>, Baja California, Mexico. On the 19th of December of 1965.
<p>
<IMG SRC="torretij.gif"> 
<p>
<li> I work at the <a href="http://bufadora.astrosen.unam.mx"> 
Observatorio  Astronomico Nacional </a> (de Mexico), 
which is part of the 
<a href="http://astroscu.unam.mx">Instituto de 
Astronomia of UNAM </a>, our national university. 
<p>
<IMG SRC="edificio.gif"> 
<p>
<li> Our offices are located in the heavenly port of 
<a href="http://www.cicese.mx/Mexico/ensenada/ensenada.html"> 
Ensenada </a>, in Baja California, Mexico.

<p>
<IMG SRC="ensenada.gif"> 
<p>

<li> Until a few months ago I was finishing my doctoral degree 
at the <a href="http://spacsun.rice.edu/spachome.html"> 
Space Physics and Astronomy Department </a> of Rice University. 

<p>

<li> Previously (in 1990) I got my bachelor's degree from the
 <a href="http://fciencias.ens.uabc.mx"> Facultad de Ciencias
 </a> of the Universidad Autonoma de Baja California  into de 
  Ensenada.
<p>
<p>
<h2> Scientific Interests </h2>
<li> <a href="http://bufadora.astrosen.unam.mx/~maurey/formacion.html">
Star Formation.</a> 
<li> Accretion Disc Physics. I am currently studying the role
 of magnetic fields in their dynamics and in the
 generation of  <a href="http://bufadora.astrosen.unam.mx/
~maurey/jetdisk.html"> collimated outflows.</a>
<li> The formation, evolution and detection of 
<a href="http://bufadora.astrosen.unam.mx/~maurey/planetas.html">
planetary systems </a> similar to ours.   
</li>
<p>

<a href="http://bufadora.astrosen.unam.mx/~maurey/resumenes/resumen.html">
