<H1>Instituto de Astronomia <BR>
Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico<BR>
</H1>
<HR>
Listed below are the currently active preprints in the collection of the
<A HREF="http://bufadora.astrosen.unam.mx">Instituto de Astronomia</A> <A HREF="http://www.unam.mx">UNAM</A>.  These are preprints
of papers written by members of this Institute and their collaborators.  All
papers in this listing have been accepted for publication, but have not yet 
appeared in print.  Copies of the abstract or text of each preprint are
available by selecting the appropriate links below.</P>
<P>Institute members may also <A HREF="http://bufadora.astrosen.unam.mx
/~maurey/preprints/prep_form.html">submit preprints</A> directly using this form.
<HR>
<h3><STRONG><EM>Can alpha-Disks Drive Winds Centrifugally ?
</EM></strong></h3>
<p>
<strong><A HREF="http://bufadora.astrosen.unam.mx/~maurey"> Reyes-Ruiz, M.</a>
y Stepinski, T.F.</strong>
<p>
We study the capability of turbulent accretion
disks to drag an external magnetic field to a configuration
favorable for driving winds centrifugally. This is done by
modeling the interaction of the large scale flow in
a geometrically thin accretion disk
with an externally imposed, uniform, vertical magnetic field.
Turbulent viscosity in the disk is given by the standard
$\alpha$ parameterization and axisymmetry is assumed. 
No attempt is made to include the back-reaction of the 
field on the disk dynamics. Solutions are obtained for 
two types of disks:
a so-called ``standard" steady-state model of a disk around
a compact star, and a steady-state model of a viscous
protoplanetary disk. The ability of the disk to drag the
field to a wind favorable configuration depends primarily
on the value of the magnetic Prandtl number for turbulent
motions, ${\cal P}_t$.
In both cases studied, no wind can be driven unless the 
Prandtl number is artificially reduced by about two orders 
of magnitude from its fiducial value of ${\cal P}_t =1$.
<BR><BR>
Expected journal of publication: 
<EM>Revista Mexicana de Astronomia y Astrofisica</EM><br>
Expected publication date: <EM>Sometime in 1995</EM>.<bR>
<BR>
Obtain a copy of this <A HREF="ftp://bufadora.astrosen.unam.mx/pub/maurey/txmxpp.ps.Z">Preprint</A><BR><BR>
<p>
<hr>
