<TR>

	<TD ALIGN=CENTER VALIGN=TOP COLSPAN="2" ROWSPAN="1">
	<FONT COLOR="#CC000C">COVER STORY / WORKING AT HOME</FONT><BR><HR>

	</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD ALIGN=RIGHT VALIGN=top COLSPAN="1" ROWSPAN="1"WIDTH="225"><IMG SRC="tech.gif" ALIGN=ABSMIDDLE WIDTH="96" HEIGHT="60" BORDER="0">
<FONT SIZE="+4">Entrepreneurial Edge</FONT>
<H3>Smart Hardware and Software to Help 
Make Your Home Business Grow BY JENNIFER DEJONG</H3><BR> <FONT SIZE="-2"></FONT>
<P>
<FONT COLOR="#CC000C"><H3 ALIGN=RIGHT>Computers, office suites, and e-mail managers -- they're among the critical tools for increasing productivity and growing your business. <BR>To get the high-technology edge, consider the products <BR>we present here.</H3></F0NT>
</P>
	<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=BOTTOM COLSPAN="1" ROWSPAN="1" WIDTH="275
	"><BR><BR><BR><BR><BR><BR><BR><BR>

<P>
<FONT SIZE="+1">
MULTIMEDIA MAESTROS
</P>

<P>
<B>Power Macintosh 7200/120 PC Compatible</B>. If you're looking for a computer
that's a cinch to set up and use, buy a Mac -- and don't worry about the
decision to do so while most of the world computes on Intel-based PCs running
Windows software. Equipped with both a PowerPC 601 processor and an Intel
Pentium processor, the Power Mac 7200/120 runs MS-DOS and Windows applications,
too. And with a single keystroke, business owners who attach a second monitor
can see documents in Macintosh, MS-DOS, or Windows applications.</FONT>
</P>

<P>
The 7200/120 has other advantages: stereo sound and the usual CD-ROM
drive, on which you'll run your favorite business-related programs -- from
Dun &amp; Bradstreet's Marketplace, for building prospect lists and doing
market research, to PhoneDisc PowerFinder 96, with its 112 million business
entries. And with the World Wide Web transforming how we conduct business,
a real bonus included here is the Apple Internet Connection Kit. This CD-ROM
makes the otherwise cumbersome task of connecting to the Net quite easy
-- guiding you through the process of getting onto the Web on the spot,
then telling you how to establish an e-mail address and an Internet account
with a service provider. The added Netscape Navigator 2.0 Web-browser software
will enable you to read and download text and graphics from the Web pages
that interest you.
</P>

<P>
The Power Macintosh 7200/120 PC Compatible runs on a 120 MHz processor;
comes with a 1.2 GB hard disk; and has 16 MB of RAM, which is expandable
to 256 MB for the Macintosh operating system, 64 MB for the 586 PC, or 72
MB for the Pentium processor (MS-DOS and Windows) -- more memory than most
home-business owners could conceivably want. Suggested retail price: $2,299
(not including a monitor or a modem). Apple Computer Inc.: 1-800-538-9696.
</P>

<P>
<B>Compaq Presario 6708.</B> A big change from earlier Presario models, which
included software titles geared to home and families and interfaces depicting
things like shopping malls, the 6708 comes with such preinstalled business-related
applications as the Microsoft Word 7.0 word-processing program and Microsoft
PowerPoint, a graphics program for creating slides and color charts useful
for business presentations, brochures, and fliers. This multimedia unit
runs on a 200 MHz Pentium processor, the fastest Intel chip on the market;
boasts a 2.5 GB hard drive; has 32 MB of RAM, expandable to 128 MB; and
comes with a 33.6-baud internal fax/modem.
</P>

<P>
Noteworthy, too, is the keyboard that doubles as a scanner. The Scanner
Keyboard sucks in paper documents, graphics, receipts, and business cards
and reproduces them onscreen. Once scanned, the electronic documents can
be faxed, copied, stored, or incorporated into software applications. PaperPort
Software, which comes with the Presario 6708, enables you to manipulate
text and graphics within scanned documents, then integrate them into presentations
or reports.
</P>

<P>
Another bonus: Face-to-face communication with colleagues and clients
-- for example, for visual conference calls or new-product demonstrations
-- is possible with Compaq's videophone-receive and -send software. Suggested
retail price: $2,999 (not including a monitor). Compaq Computer Corporation:
1-800-345-1518.
</P>

<P>
&nbsp;
</P>

<P>
<FONT SIZE="+1">SWEET OFFICE SUITES</FONT>
</P>

<P>
<B>Lotus SmartSuite 97</B> for Windows 95 and Windows NT. Even though most computers
come with at least a sampling of software programs, you can't count on getting
exactly what you need for business -- which is where office suites come
in. SmartSuite 97 offers six separate software applications that are easily
customized by users:
</P>

<P>
<DIR>
	<LI>WordPro, for word processing;
	<LI>the Approach database;
	<LI>the 1-2-3 spreadsheet;
	<LI>Freelance Graphics, for creating plans, reports, and proposals;
	<LI>Organizer, a personal-information manager for scheduling appointments
and meetings, prioritizing to-do lists, planning events, keeping an address
book, and tracking phone calls;
	<LI>and ScreenCam, a new Lotus multimedia tool that lets you create movielike
segments within documents.</DIR>
</P>

<P>
The integrated program facilitates sharing data and files between applications.
For instance, you can drag-and-drop numbers from the 1-2-3 spreadsheet into
the sales report you're drafting in WordPro, or you can mail-merge names
and addresses from the Approach database into the form letter you're sending
to prospects.
</P>

<P>
Among other features: TeamMail, which enables you to send documents from
any application without launching e-mail; TeamConsolidate, for combining
multiple files into one so you can review them together before producing
a final document; and Internet/Intranet software to help you find, publish,
and communicate online information to colleagues quickly.
</P>

<P>
Both Freelance and WordPro let you create a home page on the Web. And
Approach includes a miniapplication called SurfNet, which lists some 500
Web sites, including a business category. Suggested retail price: $399;
upgrades for earlier versions, $149. Lotus Development Corp.: 1-800-343-5414.
</P>

<P>
&nbsp;
</P>

<P>
<B>ClarisWorks 4.0</B> for Macintosh and Windows. Long popular with small-business
owners who like working within a single application rather than having to
master separate programs in a suite, ClarisWorks 4.0 includes word-processing,
spreadsheet, database, graphics, and presentation capabilities in an all-in-one
program that enables you to efficiently create everything from memos to
presentations to customer lists to mailing labels. And, as with all office
suites, you can incorporate spreadsheets, charts, graphics, and text into
one document. *
</P>

<DIR>
	<LI>Among the numerous business-support features:

	<LI>FastReport, for quick database searching and sorting;

	<LI>ExpressStyle, for formatting text, outlines, tables, and graphics;

	<LI>List View, for easy database viewing and manipulation;

	<LI>Internet authoring, with which you can create a promotional home page
	on the Web;
	<LI>and hundreds of templates, for letters, reports, invoices, newsletters,
	and more.
</DIR>

<P>
Suggested retail price: For Macs, $129; upgrades for earlier versions,
$49. For Windows, $49; upgrades, $39. Claris Corp.: 1-800-544-8554.
</P>

<P>
<FONT SIZE="+1">ELECTRONIC-MAIL 
MANAGERS</FONT>
</P>

<P>
<B>Eudora Pro 3.0</B> for Macintosh and Windows 95. An Internet-based e-mail
manager, Eudora Pro automatically sorts your messages by address, date,
or any other chosen category; has color-coded message labeling; manages
mailing lists so that with a single click, for instance, you can send a
message to a particular client; and dials in for new mail while you're working.
You can attach document files to e-mail messages from word-processing, spreadsheet,
and other applications, all of which is spell-checked before you hit the
''send'' command.
</P>

<P>
Improved text formatting offered in Eudora Pro enables users to incorporate
various fonts, font sizes, styles, colors, and layouts to give messages
a professional look. You can create multiple address books that include
e-mail lists, physical addresses, and telephone and fax numbers. New support
stationery lets you create templates for outgoing messages and use them
in automatic responses. And you can also design multiple signatures for
personalizing messages. Suggested retail price: For Mac, $89; upgrades for
earlier versions, $39. For Windows, $89; upgrades, $39. Qualcomm Inc.: 1-800-2-EUDORA.
</P>

<P>
<B>Claris Em@iler 1.1</B> for Macintosh. The Em@iler 1.1 is the only Macintosh
e-mail manager that can connect business owners to all their accounts --
not only to Internet-based accounts but also to accounts on popular services
like America Online and CompuServe. This means that the Em@iler can check
on messages and receive and manage mail from all your colleagues and clients
in one mailbox.
</P>

<P>
Among Em@iler 1.1's other features: a filing cabinet that keeps separate
folders containing messages from different individuals related to different
projects; the capability to broadcast single messages to hundreds of clients
at once; automatic mail forwarding to colleagues; and message sorting by
client, date, or other categories.
</P>

<P>
Instant notification of new messages comes by way of a customized sound
(which is useful if you're in another room and out of sight of your computer
monitor) or a symbol that flashes on your screen. Em@iler also gives you
the ability to easily attach graphics and sound files to your e-mail messages.
Suggested retail price: about $49. Claris Corp.: 1-800-544-8554.
</P>

<P>
Jennifer deJong is a Vermont-based writer specializing in technology
subjects (you can e-mail her at <A HREF="mailto:jdejong@vermontel.com">jdejong@vermontel.com</A>). 
</P></TD></TR><TR>


