<TR>

	<TD ALIGN=CENTER VALIGN=MIDDLE COLSPAN="1">
	
<FONT SIZE="+5">Pick a Winner </FONT> 

<H3>SUCCESS Magazine's Guide to Selecting a Franchise
</FONT></H3>
	</TD>
</TR>
 

	<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP COLSPAN="1" ROWSPAN="1" WIDTH="550">
	<BR><BR>

<P ALIGN=left><B>BOOK</B> </P>
<P>The Gold 100 is just the beginning. To assure franchise
riches, you need guidance -- and you need it from the experts who can help
you sort through the abundance of opportunities being offered by the franchise
industry. </P>

<P>To cut through the clutter, we offer the premier
edition of SUCCESS Magazine's Guide to Selecting a Franchise. Designed to
guide you through the decision-making process, the SUCCESS Guide includes
this year's Gold 100 survey results -- with statistical analyses and charts
detailing why these companies are the best. </P>

<P>Written for SUCCESS by franchise industry consulting
firm FRANDATA Corp. of Washington, D.C., this invaluable resource takes
you step-by-step through the challenging process of investigating and choosing
a franchise. Specific information is included on: </P>

<DIR>
	<LI><P>the most frequently asked questions about franchising</P>

	<LI><P>collecting data</P>

	<LI><P>contacting franchisors </P>

	<LI><P> examining the competition </P>

	<LI><P> reading the franchisor's documentation </P>

	<LI><P>key legal and financial issues </P>
</DIR>

<P>The guide also includes checklists to mark your
progress and detailed listings of outside resources, including Web sites,
government agencies, and professional associations. </P>


<P ALIGN=left><B>VIDEO</B> </P>
<P>How to Find the Right Franchise</P>

<P>Before you buy a franchise, ask yourself whether
you have the commitment to be an entrepreneur ''in terms of time, energy,
money, and emotional resources,'' according to Babson College professor
and former Jiffy Lube franchisee Stephen Spinelli. Skills are less critical
than the right attitude, he advises: ''If you have basic skills, franchising
can provide the rest. But I would say you have to be personally immersed
in your deal in any kind of entrepreneurship, and specifically in franchising.''
</P>

<P>Spinelli is one of numerous experts who examine
franchise issues for everyone, from beginners just finding out what franchising
offers to executives seeking to improve franchisee relations.</P>

<P>This detailed, balanced presentation spotlights
every side of franchise issues, from raising the initial investment to hot
trends. Experts from the field reveal growth segments such as business service
companies and innovative trends like co-branding, in which more than one
franchise shares space with a different -- but compatible -- franchise to
increase traffic for both. </P>

<P>Hosted by reporters from Reuters and peppered with
expert commentary, this tape moves quickly and gets deep into the issues.
It's indispensable.</P></TD>
</TR>
