<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="6" WIDTH="500">

<TR>

	<TD ALIGN=RIGHT COLSPAN="1" ROWSPAN="1" WIDTH="200">

	

<FONT SIZE="+7"><A NAME="6">Hit the Ground Running</A></FONT>



<H4>The Trials and Triumphs of Lightning-Fast Growth<BR> By Kristin Dunlap Godsey</H4>

	</TD>

	<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=BOTTOM COLSPAN="1" ROWSPAN="2" WIDTH="300">

	<IMG SRC="hit.gif" WIDTH="120" HEIGHT="120">

	</TD>

</TR>

<TR>



	<TD ALIGN=RIGHT COLSPAN="1" ROWSPAN="1" WIDTH="200"><BR><BR>

<A HREF="#1">Growth Tip #1:</A> / <A HREF="#2">Growth Tip #2:</A> / <A HREF="#3">Growth Tip #3:</A> / <A HREF="#4">Fastest-Growing Industries in the Next Decade</A> / <BR><A HREF="#5">Just For Feet's Growth Plan</A>

	</TD>

</TR>

<TR>



	<TD ALIGN=RIGHT VALIGN=TOP COLSPAN="1" ROWSPAN="1" WIDTH="200"><BR>

<A NAME=1>Growth Tip #1:<BR></A><B>Impress Your Suppliers</B>



<P><FONT COLOR=#CC000C>

Santa Monica, Calif.-based Smart Inventions Inc. made $1.8 million selling

its SmartMop in 1993. Then it made an infomercial. A year later, revenues

hit $44 million. With new products like the SmartChopper and QuickSand litter

box, Smart Inventions expects to hit $60 million in sales for 1996. Says

president Jon Nokes:

</P>



<P>

''Managing this company's growth has been a little like trying to hang

on to a runaway train. After our first test commercial, I had to go to all

my vendors and suppliers and cut deals with them to get better terms. They

were willing to help us because they stood to make a lot of money.

</P>



<P>

''The most important thing I did was to go to a retail distributor, a

company that specializes in taking television products to retail. We manufactured

the product ourselves, then shipped it to them. We had a deal where they

would express-mail the check to me within 72 hours.

</P>



<P>

''I've also tried not to take on too many projects at once. We tend to

put all our energy into one product at a time.

</P>



<P>

''While we definitely generate some money with TV sales, the infomercial

is more for educating the public. Then we put the product in the retail

stores. In this business, the general rule is that 85 percent of total sales

come from retail.

</P>



<P>

''We pound the airwaves with lots and lots of media, plus mail-order

ads. We've spent close to $1 million per month on TV for the last five months.

Everybody I talk to has seen or heard of our latest product. That's how

I know I've done my job.

</P>



<P>

''We've been able to hold on to a large percentage of the market -- despite

knockoffs -- because of our speed to retail. All our products are made in

Los Angeles. The stuff that's made in Hong Kong, Korea, or wherever takes

weeks to get here. By the time it does, we've already proved to the stores

that our items will sell and that we'll supply them with reorders quickly.

Retailers tend to be pretty loyal.''</FONT>

</P>

<BR><HR><BR><A HREF="#6"><FONT SIZE="-2">BACK TO TOP</FONT></A><BR>

<P>

<A NAME="4"><B>Fastest-Growing Industries <BR>in the Next Decade</B></A>

</P>





<TABLE BORDER="1" CELLPADDING="4" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="200">



<TR>

<TH>Industry</TH><TH>Size of Dominant Firms</TH>

</TR>

<TR>



	<TD ALIGN=CENTER VALIGN=TOP COLSPAN="1" ROWSPAN="1" WIDTH="200">

	Mfg. of computer equipment

	</TD>

	<TD ALIGN=CENTER VALIGN=TOP COLSPAN="1" ROWSPAN="1" WIDTH="200">

	large

	</TD>

</TR>

<TR>



	<TD ALIGN=CENTER VALIGN=TOP COLSPAN="1" ROWSPAN="1" WIDTH="200">

	Mfg. of semiconductors, related devices

	</TD>

	<TD ALIGN=CENTER VALIGN=TOP COLSPAN="1" ROWSPAN="1" WIDTH="200">

	large

	</TD>

</TR>

<TR>



	<TD ALIGN=CENTER VALIGN=TOP COLSPAN="1" ROWSPAN="1" WIDTH="200">

	Residential care

	</TD>

	<TD ALIGN=CENTER VALIGN=TOP COLSPAN="1" ROWSPAN="1" WIDTH="200">

	small

	</TD>

</TR>

<TR>



	<TD ALIGN=CENTER VALIGN=TOP COLSPAN="1" ROWSPAN="1" WIDTH="200">

	Health services

	</TD>

	<TD ALIGN=CENTER VALIGN=TOP COLSPAN="1" ROWSPAN="1" WIDTH="200">

