<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#095A24" ALINK="#FF0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<BR><BR><CENTER><P><FONT COLOR="#CC000C">EDITOR'S NOTE </FONT></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P>BY SCOTT DeGARMO </P></CENTER><BR><BR>

<FONT SIZE="+4" ALIGN=CENTER>The Power of Great Comebacks</FONT>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Down but not Defeated, Entrepreneurs Won't Succumb </H3><BR>

<P>Dave Bruno awoke to see faces with surgical masks looking down at him.
As he lost consciousness again, he thought, ''I'm going to die.'' </P>

<P>Despite his smashed body, doctors saved him. He spent three days hooked
up to tubes. For some reason, his heart was racing at a dangerous rate.
Bruno's wife, Marlene, was told he might die. He thought so, too, but there
was one thing he had to know. Unable to speak, he gestured for a pencil
and paper and scribbled a message: Was anyone else hurt? </P>

<P>On hearing that he was the only one in the crash, his heart rate quickly
dropped to normal. He'd been living with the terror he had killed or injured
others. Prior to the accident, he'd gotten burned out. His mother had died
of lung cancer. His newly born son had a severe case of strep. And then,
he'd lost his job as a national sales manager. </P>

<P>He was driving home at night when his car veered off the road and crashed.
As Bruno recovered, a vision of inspiring others took shape in his mind.
He remembered how his mother would place quotations around the house and
on the refrigerator. They lifted spirits, focused attention, and united
the family in meeting common challenges. Bruno found the quotations invaluable
after his father died and he had to drop out of school to help support
his mother and sisters. When he discovered the Napoleon Hill classic, Think
and Grow Rich, his mother typed up passages from the book. Now Bruno vowed
he would find a way to use such uplifting ideas in a product. </P>

<P>The truth was, however, he had no concept of how to turn his vision
into a business. And for the moment, life looked grim. He had spent 10
years working his way up in sales. On losing his job, he also lost his
health insurance; and bills from the accident plunged him into personal
bankruptcy. He and Marlene and their three sons had to move out of their
attractive suburban Milwaukee home and into a cramped apartment. </P>

<P>While delivering pizzas and magazines on the side, he took a series
of jobs to learn about advertising. Then, he rented a hellhole of a shop
in a former tannery -- it stank -- where he could hear gunfire at night
as he struggled to master the basics of printing. He thanked God Marlene
believed in him, because he was bombarded with criticism from friends and
family. Why didn't he get a job? What made him think he could run a business?
Deeply wounded, he persevered. Then came the day when Marlene called from
home, hysterical. They had $90 in their bank account, and the Internal
Revenue Service was taking it. The next step he took to survive nearly
shattered him. </P>

<P>Among the jobs he took to make ends meet, Bruno had a paper route with
his sons. His oldest boy had saved $1,000. He'd counseled the boy on the
importance of saving. He recalled the words of Napoleon Hill: ''A man who
cannot save money does not have the seeds of success within him.'' It was
bad enough that they had sacrificed so much, that Marlene was strapped
with baby-sitting 12 children at a time, that Christmas now meant presents
bought with borrowed money and wrapped in newspaper. Now, with tears filling
his eyes, he asked his son to empty his bank account so the family could
eat. </P>

<P>His turnaround came at his lowest moment, as he spent the night on the
battered couch in his pitiful shop, reliving the events that had sent him
to the brink of desperation. ''I was lying there crying, thinking I wasn't
a good provider. Then I saw the wall where I had hung the cover of SUCCESS's
'Great Comebacks' issue. I recalled Hill's words: 'What the mind of man
can conceive and believe it can achieve.' It was incredibly powerful. I
knew I had to commit to do whatever it took to make my dream come true.''
</P>

<P>With renewed commitment, Bruno's fortunes swiftly turned around. He
perfected a method of printing his classic quotes on gold cards, arranged
in categories. He also discovered a huge potential customer base. Soon,
he was selling tens of thousands of cards to major corporations such as
3M, Nabisco, Harley-Davidson, and Johnson Wax. He began customizing them
with company logos for use as giveaways and premiums. </P>

<P>Today, Bruno and Marlene, with help from their sons, work from home
in comfortable circumstances. He wrote me recently, to say he had sold
his one-millionth card and that his business was on the verge of a major
expansion. </P>

<P>Out of his entire rich library of quotes -- the result of years of cataloging
the world's best -- his favorite saying is from Henry Ford: Whether you
think you can or can't -- you are right. </P>

<P>To get information on obtaining Bruno's gold cards for use as business
gifts or staff motivators, phone him at: 1-800-870-4410. His fax is: 414-529-1648.
</P>

<P>You also might simply want to tell him, Congratulations! <BR><BR>

<HR><BR>
